29/07/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- During his visit to Macedonia on Thursday (28 July), Admiral Harry Ulrich, commander of the Allied Joint Force Command Naples, praised the progress made in defence reforms and the commitment shown to the international community by participation in various missions. Ulrich met with Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski and Defence Minister Jovan Manasijevski to discuss regional co-operation and the domestic security situation. The parties agreed that Macedonia faces no threats to its stability. Buckovski expressed the hope that the country will be invited to join NATO by the end of 2006. (Government of Macedonia Web site, MIA - 28/07/05)
